data.chText: 羊毛；（一只羊一次剪下的）毛
data.enText: the wool coat of a sheep; this coat when it has been removed from a sheep (by shearing )

data.chText: 羊毛状织物；绒头织物短上衣；绒头织物运动衫
data.enText: a type of soft warm cloth that feels like sheep's wool; a jacket or sweatshirt that is made from this cloth
to take a lot of money from sb by charging them too much

data.chText: 有些当地商店一直在敲旅游者的竹杠。
data.enText: Some local shops have been fleecing tourists.

tr: outer coat of especially sheep and yaks
a soft bulky fabric with deep pile
tanned skin of a sheep with the fleece left on
the wool of a sheep or similar animal

value.def: A sheep's fleece is the coat of wool that covers it.
A fleece is the wool that is cut off one sheep in a single piece.
value.tran: 一只羊一次剪下的羊毛

value.def: If you fleece someone, you get a lot of money from them by tricking them or charging them too much.

example.ex: She claims he fleeced her out of thousands of pounds.
example.tran: 她声称他敲诈了她几千英镑。

value.def: Fleece is a soft warm artificial fabric. A fleece is also a jacket or other garment made from this fabric.
value.tran: 绒头织物;绒头织物服装
